Based on the same principles as acupuncture, (but using pressure instead of needles), acupressure works by stimulating specific reflex points located along the lines of energy which run through the body, called meridians. There are 14 main meridian lines and numerous secondary lines, each of which corresponds to an individual organ or physical system of the body. When the vital energies (ki) are able to flow through the meridians in a balanced and even way, the result is good health.
